text:
I love the InstaCash feature.  It's true you have a due date, but they are knocking down my door to get their money and I've owed them for far too long.  Now, I know and feel confident they are on my team.  I am going to pay them back, but my finances are forced at this moment to be closer to liquid than move it around to try and make a deposit at MoneyLion bank.  They offer like 3 ways to deposit money into the account.  They are an internet bank, that has no branches.  I have gotten used to this, but it could be a deal-breaker for some.  Usually, internet banks have excellent customer service over the phone.  I'm depositing money through direct deposit a little, but my banks don't work with MoneyLion Bank.  My old one did and didn't also.  MoneyLion could correct this with another deposit method.  The cashier at participating store deposit.  Hand cash to Cashier and like loading a prepaid card you make a deposit into your account.  It's not that hard and can be very convenient.  I appreciate MoneyLion a lot.  I have my end of the week DoorDash and end of week Postmates direct deposit connected to Moneylion, no problems.  Cash-out is assigned to another bank.  It's interesting decisions, cash out or deposit $ to pay of InstaCash :)     I choose to pay off awesome no interest almost no fee money advance.   Thank you,  International money wires would be great to receive at least, maybe.   Thank you,
Thank you,
Daniel Morgan
